parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
symptoms: The parking brake fails to hold the vehicle
the parking brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the parking brake makes a grinding or scraping noise
the parking brake warning light illuminates
the vehicle slips or rolls from a parked position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to severe injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not provided with the necessary protection to mitigate the impact.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact
resulting in injuries or fatalities to occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Anti-Lock Brake (ABS) Failure due to Corrosion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause unwanted ABS activation, increased stopping distance, and reduced vehicle control, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: increased stopping distance during low-speed brake application
brake pedal goes to the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to be unable to stop, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Metal Contamination
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of metal in the oil can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potential safety hazards.
The failure of the ABS control module can cause the ABS system to malfunction, leading to reduced vehicle control and increased stopping distance.
The failure of the brake pads can cause the vehicle to be unable to stop, leading to accidents or injuries.
The faulty transmission shifting can cause the vehicle to hesitate or jerk when shifting gears, leading to loss of control, accidents, or damage to the rear differential and drive shaft.
symptoms: hesitation or jerking when shifting gears
gear shifter difficult to move or stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear driveshaft or propeller shaft can cause the transmission to shift roughly, leading to damage to the rear differential and drive shaft, and potentially causing loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: hesitation or jerking when shifting gears
rear end of the vehicle feels loose.
